'''Helen Prest-Ajayi''',  formerly '''Prest-Davies''', ([[née]] '''Prest''', born 17 September 1960)<ref>{{cite web|url=  http://www.bellanaija.com/2009/10/24/helen-prest-ajayi-hosts-a-grand-soiree-as-she-celebrates-her-50th-birthday/|title=Helen Prest Ajayi hosts a grand soiree as she celebrates her 50th birthday| website=Bella Naija|date=24 October 2009|accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref> is a Nigerian lawyer, writer and former beauty queen.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nigerianbestforum.com/blog/metamorphosis-of-beauty-queens/|title=METAMORPHOSIS OF BEAUTY QUEENS|publisher=NBF News|author=Josfyn Uba|author2=Kate Hakim |date=22 January 2011|accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://theunion.com.ng/helen-prest-ajayi-giving-back-to-the-society-through-education/|title=Helen Prest Ajayi: Giving back to Society through education|accessdate=1 June 2014}}</ref>
Helen was raised in England. She attended the [[International School Ibadan]] for her advanced levels and [[Obafemi Awolowo University]] for her undergraduate studies in Law prior to her pageantry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenet.ng/i-continued-look-glam-58-•-beauty-queen-helen-prest-ajayi/|date=April 16, 2018|website=Nigerian Entertainment Today|title=How I Have Continued To Look GLAM At 58 • Beauty Queen, Helen Prest-Ajayi}}</ref> After she was crowned [[Miss Nigeria]] at the age of 19 in 1979, she represented Nigeria at the [[Miss World]] pageant and furthered her education at [[King's College London]], earning an LLM. She was also active as a columnist in the 1990s.
She is currently the CEO of Media Business Company.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.punchng.com/spice/personalities/simplicity-is-style-helen-prest-ajayi/ |title=Simplicity is style |author=Kemi Ashfon |date=5 January 2014 |publisher=The Punch |accessdate=1 June 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140602111715/http://www.punchng.com/spice/personalities/simplicity-is-style-helen-prest-ajayi/ |archivedate=2 June 2014 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
She is the granddaughter of Nigerian politician [[Arthur Prest]]. She married Tosin Ajayi and has three daughters. 

