{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}} {{Use British English|date=May 2013}} {{Infobox writer | name = Mortimer Baidgent Devot | pseudonym = MB Devot | birth_name = | birth_date = 10 April 1934 | birth_place = [[Chepstow]], [[Monmouthshire]] | death_date = 9 June 1987 | death_place = | nationality = English | ethnicity = | citizenship = UK | education = Eton College | alma_mater = Trinity College, Cambridge | period = | genre = psychic phenomena, natural history, forteana | subject = | movement = | notableworks = A Microphone in the Hedgerow | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | website = | portaldisp = }}
'''Mortimer Baidgent Devot''' writing as '''MB Devot''' ( 10 April 1934 – 9 June 1987 <ref name=Times>''The Times'' 12 June 1987 "MB Devot"</ref>) was an [[England|English]] author, [[physics|physicist]], amateur [[natural history|naturalist]] and [[Western esotericism|esotericist]]. During the 1960s and 70s his writing attempted to account for psychic phenomena as a result of electromagnetic fields and acoustic effects acting on the human brain. In later life, he pursued a synthesis of his early theses and his newer interests in the seemingly diverse subjects of [[folklore]], [[natural history]], [[psychoacoustics]] and [[eternity|eternalism]].<ref name=ForteanTimes53>''Fortean Times'' #53 Autumn 1989 "MB Devot, A Life in the Hedgerow"</ref>
