This is a '''partial filmography of Prem Nazir'''.<ref>http://en.msidb.org/displayProfile.php?category=actors&artist=Prem%20Nazeer</ref> [[Prem Nazir]] is an Indian actor who worked primarily in [[Malayalam cinema]] films.<ref>http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/movieslist.php?a=45</ref>Nazir holds two [[Guinness World Records]]; for playing the lead role in a record 725 films,<ref>{{cite book|title=Kisan World|year=1989|publisher=Sakthi Sugars, Limited}}</ref><ref>[http://www.hindu.com/mag/2003/11/02/stories/2003110200250500.htm "Magic of Sophia Loren"]. The Hindu (2 November 2003). Retrieved 3 December 2011.</ref> and for playing opposite the same heroine in 130 films (with [[Sheela]]),<ref>{{cite book|title=Guinness World Records 2001|page=91|publisher=[[Guinness World Records]]|isbn=0553583751|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HasxAQAAIAAJ&q=prem+nazir+guinness+world+record&dq=prem+nazir+guinness+world+record&hl=en&sa=X&ei=TkZIU-3rNoquiAfg04GgAw&ved=0CE8Q6AEwBw}}</ref><ref>[http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/thscrip/print.pl?file=2004010500340200.htm&date=2004/01/05/&prd=mp& Sheela's comeback]. The Hindu. 05/01/2004. Retrieved 3 December 2011.</ref> He also holds two other acting records in the Indian film industry; for acting opposite eighty heroines and for acting in lead roles in thirty nine films which were released in a single year (1979).<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0623427/bio Biography for Prem Nazir]. Internet Movie Database</ref><ref name="greatestactor">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2009/01/16/stories/2009011650650100.htm|title=The evergreen hero|work= The Hindu|accessdate=11 March 2011|location=Chennai, India|date=16 January 2009}}</ref>
